parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Instrument Panel and Electrical System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument panel and electrical system can lead to inaccurate or missing information, causing the driver to be unaware of critical vehicle conditions, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: and check oil lights stay on
electrical lights in the dash not working
and issues with the driver information center.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag light staying on, which can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of an accident, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: airbag sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the engine and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or have difficulty stopping, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: car won't crank in low temperatures
and car stops when putting foot on the brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on and stays on
the airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash
especially if the steering wheel is turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, including the airbag system, temperature gauge, and radio dashboard lights, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: the radio dashboard lights go out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can increase the risk of accidents, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while sitting at a yield sign or in traffic
the vehicle is rear-ended by oncoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult or impossible to steer, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering becomes tight or locks
especially at low speeds or when parking; clunking noise in the steering; loss of power steering when the serpentine belt slips; extremely difficult steering at low speeds
especially when the vehicle is at operating temperature.
